<subSubSection pageId="272" pageNumber="273" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="272.[151,1437,1592,2015]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1592,1619]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<specimenCount box="[281,302,1593,1619]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1893" box="[340,435,1593,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Bocchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[340,435,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Bocchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with antennomere 6 less than twice as long as broad; mesoscutum reticulate rugose (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 104" captionStartId="271.[151,250,1740,1765]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,253,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@271.[151,1436,265,1728]" captionTargetPageId="271" captionText="FIGURE 104. Habitus of Bocchus species. A: B. forestalis Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., ♂ holotype in dorsal view; head vertex sculpture. B–D: B. granulatus Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., ♂ holotype: habitus in dorsal (B) and lateral (C) view; head and mesosoma in dorsal view (D). E: B. harinhalai Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., ♂ holotype in dorsal view; head vertex sculpture. F: B. hova Olmi, ♂ holotype in dorsal view. Scale bar: A: 3.0 mm; D: 0.88 mm; F: 1.62 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3336880/files/figure.png" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Fig. 104E</figureCitation>
); notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.6 × length of mesoscutum; propodeal declivity with median area as reticulate rugose as lateral areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="273" lastPageNumber="274" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="272.[151,1437,1592,2015]" lastBlockId="273.[151,1437,153,323]" lastPageId="273" lastPageNumber="274" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1700,1727]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Description.</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[351,372,1701,1727]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation box="[387,506,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 104" captionStartId="271.[151,250,1740,1765]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,253,1722]" captionTargetId="figure@271.[151,1436,265,1728]" captionTargetPageId="271" captionText="FIGURE 104. Habitus of Bocchus species. A: B. forestalis Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., ♂ holotype in dorsal view; head vertex sculpture. B–D: B. granulatus Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., ♂ holotype: habitus in dorsal (B) and lateral (C) view; head and mesosoma in dorsal view (D). E: B. harinhalai Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., ♂ holotype in dorsal view; head vertex sculpture. F: B. hova Olmi, ♂ holotype in dorsal view. Scale bar: A: 3.0 mm; D: 0.88 mm; F: 1.62 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3336880/files/figure.png" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Figs 104E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[516,562,1700,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 105" captionStartId="273.[151,250,1789,1814]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,342,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@273.[151,1436,337,1777]" captionTargetPageId="273" captionText="FIGURE 105. Bocchus harinhalai Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., ♂ holotype: habitus in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) view; mesosoma in dorsal (C) view; head in frontal view (D); forewing (E); genital armature (F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3336882/files/figure.png" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">105</figureCitation>
). Fully winged; body length 
<quantity box="[883,972,1701,1727]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna brown-testaceous; mesosoma black; metasoma brown-black; legs brown, except articulations, tarsi and protibia testaceous. Antenna filiform; antennomeres in following proportions: 11:5:7:7:6:6:6:5:5:8; antennomere 6 less than twice as long as broad (6:4). Head (Fig. 1059D) convex, dull, covered with short setae, completely strongly reticulate rugose; frontal line complete, weakly convex between antennal toruli; occipital carina complete; POL = 5; OL = 2; OOL = 7.5; OPL = 5; TL = 5; greatest breadth of lateral ocelli longer than OL (3:2). Mesoscutum (Fig. 1059C) dull, completely strongly reticulate rugose. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.6 × length of mesoscutum. Mesoscutellum dull, reticulate rugose. Metanotum rugose. Mesopleuron dull, strongly reticulate rugose. Metapleuron dull, sculptured by numerous strong transverse keels. Metapectal-propodeal disc with strong transverse posterior keel, dull, reticulate rugose; propodeal declivity dull, with two complete longitudinal keels, median area as rugose as lateral areas. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[714,827,188,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 105" captionStartId="273.[151,250,1789,1814]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,342,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@273.[151,1436,337,1777]" captionTargetPageId="273" captionText="FIGURE 105. Bocchus harinhalai Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., ♂ holotype: habitus in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) view; mesosoma in dorsal (C) view; head in frontal view (D); forewing (E); genital armature (F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3336882/files/figure.png" pageId="273" pageNumber="274">Fig. 105E</figureCitation>
) hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of 2r-rs&amp;Rs vein shorter than proximal part (8:9); 2R1 cell open. Apex of basivolsella slender and with subdistal inner pointed apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[370,482,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 108" captionStartId="278.[151,250,1873,1898]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,667,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@278.[151,1436,661,1861]" captionTargetPageId="278" captionText="FIGURE 108. ♂ genitalia of Bocchus species. A: B. granulatus Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., holotype. B: B. harin- halai Olmi, Copeland &amp; van Noort sp. nov., holotype. C: B. hova Olmi, ♂ from Madagascar, 21°15.99’S 47°25.21’E. D: B. hyalinus Olmi, ♂ from Oman, Al-Uyaina-Samail. E: B. incompletus Olmi, holotype. F: B. irwini Olmi &amp; Guglielmino, paratype. Scale bar: A: 0.09 mm; B, D: 0.13 mm; C: 0.06 mm; E: 0.07 mm; F: 0.17 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3336890/files/figure.png" pageId="273" pageNumber="274">Fig. 108B</figureCitation>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[483,498,260,287]" pageId="273" pageNumber="274">).</emphasis>
Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="273.[151,1437,153,323]" box="[199,352,297,323]" pageId="273" pageNumber="274">♀. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3336882/files/figure.png" pageId="273" pageNumber="274" startId="273.[151,250,1789,1814]" targetBox="[156,1431,342,1776]" targetPageId="273">
<paragraph blockId="273.[151,1436,1789,1850]" pageId="273" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,300,1789,1814]" pageId="273" pageNumber="274">FIGURE 105.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[305,503,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="273" pageNumber="274">Bocchus harinhalai</emphasis>
